56
00:04:55,268 --> 00:04:58,032
It's not that.
It would be like...

57
00:04:58,104 --> 00:05:01,232
rewarding us
for bad behavior.

58
00:05:01,307 --> 00:05:03,867
- But if you really want to.
- No, Joe.

59
00:05:03,943 --> 00:05:06,673
It wouldn't be right
to take advantage of Ben like that.

60
00:05:06,746 --> 00:05:08,680
No pizza for us.

61
00:05:08,748 --> 00:05:11,216
Okay.

62
00:05:20,527 --> 00:05:22,461
Ice cream?

63
00:05:24,497 --> 00:05:27,227
So, now I don't know
if I'll ever find out who my father is.

64
00:05:29,802 --> 00:05:35,104
Maybe she figured
you weren't ready for the truth.

65
00:05:35,175 --> 00:05:37,040
Ben?

66
00:05:38,611 --> 00:05:40,738
Do you know the truth?

67
00:05:40,813 --> 00:05:45,477
No. I guess your mom was just
gonna tell me when she was ready.

68
00:05:48,988 --> 00:05:52,924
But if you did know,
would you tell me?

69
00:05:55,428 --> 00:05:57,658
Yeah.

70
00:05:57,730 --> 00:06:00,164
Yes, I would.

71
00:06:00,233 --> 00:06:03,066
Ben?

72
00:06:03,136 --> 00:06:06,503
Did Miss Wenteworth
ever talk about me?

73
00:06:06,573 --> 00:06:08,507
All the time, Simon.

74
00:06:08,575 --> 00:06:10,634
Everybody talks about you.

75
00:06:10,710 --> 00:06:12,735
That's how we keep
from gettin' bored.

76
00:06:12,812 --> 00:06:15,303
- Did she tell you about my destiny?
- Simon!

77
00:06:15,381 --> 00:06:17,406
What do you mean?

78
00:06:17,483 --> 00:06:19,576
- I'm going to be a hero.
- You are?

79
00:06:19,652 --> 00:06:22,780
Pretty vague job description,
isn't it?

80
00:06:22,855 --> 00:06:26,985
- How you gonna do that?
- I don't know.

81
00:06:27,060 --> 00:06:28,994
I keep waiting for God
to show me a sign.

82
00:06:29,062 --> 00:06:31,963
Like the burning bush
in the Ten Commandments.

83
00:06:34,033 --> 00:06:37,434
But I guess he doesn't go in
for that kind of thing anymore.

84
00:06:37,503 --> 00:06:40,802
Well, uh, you know,
you got to be a little patient.

85
00:06:40,873 --> 00:06:45,037
I have been patient,
but I'm running out of time.

86
00:06:45,111 --> 00:06:49,605
Simon, you're
12 years old!

87
00:06:49,682 --> 00:06:51,616
You've got all the time
in the world!

88
00:06:54,320 --> 00:06:56,880
I don't think so, Ben.

89
00:07:06,432 --> 00:07:11,369
<i>Time is a monster
that cannot be reasoned with.</i>

90
00:07:11,437 --> 00:07:15,271
<i>It responds like
a snail to our impatience.</i>

91
00:07:15,341 --> 00:07:19,778
<i>Then it races like a gazelle
when you can't catch your breath.</i>

92
00:07:19,846 --> 00:07:23,043
<i>Simon and I were in such a hurry
to get to the answers at the end...</i>

93
00:07:23,116 --> 00:07:26,347
<i>of the road that we never took time
to read the signs along the way.</i>

94
00:07:27,320 --> 00:07:31,256
<i>How could we have known that everything
was working together for a reason?</i>

95
00:07:31,324 --> 00:07:33,724
And so I expect
each and every one of you...

96
00:07:33,793 --> 00:07:35,988
will lend a hand
in making this...

97
00:07:36,062 --> 00:07:38,826
the best Christmas
pageant ever.

98
00:07:41,901 --> 00:07:44,563
So, now, are there
any volunteers for roles,

99
00:07:44,637 --> 00:07:48,164
- or shall I just choose?
- Well, I'll play Joseph!

100
00:07:48,241 --> 00:07:50,209
Good for you, Eddie.

101
00:07:50,276 --> 00:07:53,074
- Looks like I got the lead.
- What lead?

102
00:07:53,146 --> 00:07:55,080
It's the Virgin Mary, Eddie.

103
00:07:55,148 --> 00:07:57,548
What does Joseph
have to do with anything?

104
00:07:57,617 --> 00:08:00,211
All right, now.
Any volunteers for Mary?

105
00:08:00,286 --> 00:08:03,050
Beautiful, beautiful
Mother Mary.

106
00:08:05,925 --> 00:08:08,485
Mary, Mary, Mary.

107
00:08:08,561 --> 00:08:10,495
Who will it be?

108
00:08:17,303 --> 00:08:19,237
Marjorie?

109
00:08:19,305 --> 00:08:21,796
Would you like to be
our Mary this year?

110
00:08:21,874 --> 00:08:25,275
- Yes, ma'am.
- Good girl!

111
00:08:27,347 --> 00:08:29,713
All right, now.
Which one of our...

112
00:08:29,782 --> 00:08:34,020
future stars
would like to be the Three Wise Men?

113
00:08:34,153 --> 00:08:36,121
Hm?

114
00:08:36,188 --> 00:08:38,554
Three Wise Men.
Who's it gonna be?

115
00:08:38,624 --> 00:08:40,558
All right.

116
00:08:40,626 --> 00:08:45,962
Gary, Allen, Matthew,
you will be the Wise Men.

117
00:08:46,032 --> 00:08:48,193
Now let's see what we've got.

118
00:08:48,267 --> 00:08:50,462
Ah, well, we've got
the shepherds,

119
00:08:50,536 --> 00:08:52,663
but they don't have
a lot to do.

120
00:08:52,738 --> 00:08:55,138
<i>Miss Leavey
always tried to downplay...</i>

121
00:08:55,207 --> 00:08:57,641
<i>the role of the shepherds,
but we weren't fooled.</i>

122
00:08:57,710 --> 00:09:01,271
<i>We knew they were the plum roles
because all you had to do...</i>

123
00:09:01,347 --> 00:09:03,577
<i>was stand around with a staff
and try not to laugh...</i>

124
00:09:03,649 --> 00:09:06,174
<i>at the poor saps that got stuck
with the speaking parts.</i>

125
00:09:06,252 --> 00:09:08,516
All right.
Hands-Hands down. Hands down.

126
00:09:08,587 --> 00:09:12,648
Uh, Joe, Melanie,
Ming, Tommy.

127
00:09:12,725 --> 00:09:17,424
You will be
our shepherds.

128
00:09:17,496 --> 00:09:19,430
All right.
Now, let's see what's next.

129
00:09:19,498 --> 00:09:21,796
We've got...
Oh, the angel.

130
00:09:21,867 --> 00:09:23,801
Yes, the angel.

131
00:09:23,869 --> 00:09:27,930
The wonderful angel
of the Lord...

132
00:09:28,007 --> 00:09:32,637
suspended high, high above
everyone else...

133
00:09:32,711 --> 00:09:37,978
the wonderful, magnificent angel
of the Lord.

134
00:09:39,051 --> 00:09:40,985
Aww!

135
00:09:41,053 --> 00:09:43,487
- I can't! I'm afraid of heights!
- Well, then, this will be...

136
00:09:43,556 --> 00:09:45,490
the perfect chance
to face your fears.

137
00:09:45,558 --> 00:09:47,788
- Can't I be a donkey or somethin'?
- You're an angel.

138
00:09:47,860 --> 00:09:50,954
You have your own special pillar
of light for all the world to see.

139
00:09:51,030 --> 00:09:53,965
- Well, I'll switch with Howard.
- No!
- Yeah!

140
00:09:54,033 --> 00:09:55,830
- I could be Joseph. Joseph does nothing.
- Told ya.

141
00:09:55,901 --> 00:09:58,995
You are going to make
a wonderful angel, Howard.

142
00:09:59,071 --> 00:10:03,007
- But...
- Thank you.

143
00:10:03,075 --> 00:10:07,136
- Psycho.
- What about me?

144
00:10:07,213 --> 00:10:10,341
Well, Simon, you know what?

145
00:10:10,416 --> 00:10:13,476
- You have the most important
role of all.
- No.

146
00:10:13,552 --> 00:10:16,112
Without you,
there would be no play.

147
00:10:16,188 --> 00:10:18,748
I'm not playing the baby Jesus,
so just forget it!

148
00:10:18,824 --> 00:10:21,554
- You're the only one
who fits into the manger.
- I won't do it!

149
00:10:21,627 --> 00:10:24,425
Come on, Simon.
It'll be fun.

150
00:10:35,074 --> 00:10:39,909
Easy! It says swaddling clothes.
Swaddle it!

151
00:10:39,979 --> 00:10:42,880
Simon, that is so cute!

152
00:10:42,948 --> 00:10:46,111
I look like a burn victim.

153
00:10:47,753 --> 00:10:50,620
- You made her laugh.
- She's laughing at me.

154
00:10:50,689 --> 00:10:52,919
What's the difference?
She likes you.

155
00:10:52,992 --> 00:10:55,756
Everyone likes
the swaddling baby Jesus.

156
00:10:55,828 --> 00:10:57,853
- It's great!
- You really like it? Well, thank you.

157
00:10:57,930 --> 00:11:00,455
Why does Ming get
all the girls?

158
00:11:01,667 --> 00:11:03,601
But, uh, things
will be different...

159
00:11:03,669 --> 00:11:05,603
once God makes you
a hero, right, Simon?

160
00:11:12,611 --> 00:11:15,239
- Right?
- Huh?

161
00:11:15,314 --> 00:11:18,750
Oh, yeah.
I guess.

162
00:11:18,817 --> 00:11:22,548
You! You, you, you,
you, you, you! Okay, okay. Come on.

163
00:11:22,621 --> 00:11:25,249
So, is everybody ready
for dress rehearsal?

164
00:11:25,324 --> 00:11:27,485
- No.
- What now, Simon?

165
00:11:27,560 --> 00:11:29,585
What are those?

166
00:11:29,662 --> 00:11:32,460
- They're turtledoves.
- They look like
they're from outer space.

167
00:11:32,531 --> 00:11:34,465
The audience won't know
what they are.

168
00:11:34,533 --> 00:11:37,991
They're doves, Simon!
The audience knows what a dove is!

169
00:11:38,070 --> 00:11:41,437
They're giant doves!
They're as big as half a donkey!

170
00:11:41,507 --> 00:11:43,441
They're actually
kind of frightening!

171
00:11:43,509 --> 00:11:48,208
Oh, look what I found
wandering off. A turtle.

172
00:11:48,280 --> 00:11:50,714
Oh! A little turtledove! Look at that.

173
00:11:50,783 --> 00:11:54,048
Oh, so how's
the rehearsal going?

174
00:11:54,119 --> 00:11:59,182
Help. Please! I'm gonna strangle him.

175
00:11:59,258 --> 00:12:01,624
I swear to God! I'm gonna strangle
that little granite mouse...

176
00:12:01,694 --> 00:12:03,628
if it's the last thing I do,
with my bare hands!

177
00:12:03,696 --> 00:12:06,256
- I'm gonna strangle him!
I'm a little fragile right now.
- Simon.

178
00:12:26,185 --> 00:12:29,120
- Hey!
- You'll get these back
after the pageant.

179
00:12:29,188 --> 00:12:31,679
If you can stop yourself
from ruining our play.

180
00:12:31,757 --> 00:12:33,691
Understand?

181
00:12:38,097 --> 00:12:40,031
Any questions?

182
00:12:42,601 --> 00:12:45,069
Does God have
a plan for us?

183
00:12:50,409 --> 00:12:52,343
I like to think he does.

184
00:12:52,411 --> 00:12:56,245
Me too! I think God made me
the way I am for a reason.

185
00:12:56,315 --> 00:13:01,378
Well, I'm glad that, um,
that your faith, uh...

186
00:13:01,453 --> 00:13:04,581
helps you deal
with your, um,

187
00:13:04,657 --> 00:13:07,091
you know,
your-your condition.

188
00:13:07,159 --> 00:13:09,491
That's not what I mean.

189
00:13:09,561 --> 00:13:12,359
I think I'm
God's instrument.

190
00:13:12,431 --> 00:13:15,229
That He's gonna use me
to carry out His plan.

191
00:13:15,301 --> 00:13:17,326
It's wonderful
to have faith, Simon,

192
00:13:17,403 --> 00:13:21,271
but, uh,
let's not overdo it.

193
00:13:36,655 --> 00:13:39,180
God's instrument.

194
00:13:45,560 --> 00:13:48,924
Hey, kid. You okay?

195
00:13:49,001 --> 00:13:53,028
- Hey, kid.
- Hi. What's wrong?

196
00:13:54,540 --> 00:13:57,737
My dad's makin' me go
on a retreat tomorrow.

197
00:13:57,810 --> 00:14:01,610
- Why are you crying?
- I'm scared of all the other kids.

198
00:14:01,680 --> 00:14:03,614
They're a lot
bigger than me.

199
00:14:03,682 --> 00:14:07,709
- Not all of them.
- Are you going too?

200
00:14:07,786 --> 00:14:10,687
And I'll make sure
nothing happens to you. I promise.

201
00:14:10,756 --> 00:14:14,089
Now get over there with those other
flying monkeys where you belong.

202
00:14:14,159 --> 00:14:17,925
We're turtledoves.

203
00:14:17,996 --> 00:14:21,056
Quack. Quack.

204
00:14:21,133 --> 00:14:24,694
- You're good with him.
- Little kids always listen to me...

205
00:14:24,770 --> 00:14:27,671
because of the way I look.

206
00:14:27,740 --> 00:14:31,267
- Too bad Marjorie isn't six years old.
- Not funny!

207
00:14:31,510 --> 00:14:34,536
The star of Bethlehem
is not a pinata.

208
00:14:34,613 --> 00:14:37,241
Marjorie! Marjorie!
You spit that gum out right now!

209
00:14:37,316 --> 00:14:39,250
The Virgin Mary
does not chew gum.

210
00:14:39,318 --> 00:14:42,014
Where are we going?
You get down from there!

211
00:14:42,087 --> 00:14:44,021
Get down from there now!
It's not safe!

212
00:14:44,089 --> 00:14:46,853
I've got half a donkey here.
What good is that gonna do me?

213
00:14:48,660 --> 00:14:51,185
I need a cigarette.

214
00:14:52,264 --> 00:14:55,427
Monsters.

215
00:15:10,115 --> 00:15:12,049
Oh! Oh, hello, Agnes.

216
00:15:12,117 --> 00:15:15,644
Hello, Reverend. Hi.

217
00:15:15,721 --> 00:15:17,655
Ah, ready for tonight?

218
00:15:17,723 --> 00:15:19,657
Absolutely.

